          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Summarize (Orchestrating the Discussion)</strong></p><p><em>Solutions and Strategies</em></p><p>Have students discuss the rate tables.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILEQ2KVx-FHCZTA",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Suggested Questions</strong></p><p>If students do not explicitly mention the role of the unit rate, push them to think about it with these questions. (Language)</p><ul><li>Which tables were easier for you to complete, the tables in Problem 3.1 or these?</li><li>How can the unit rate help you find equivalent ratios in the table? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "TILEcaFCPdU2GfrY",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Most likely students will think that the patterns in this problem were easier. Students should mention using multiples of 4 or adding 4 more cups for each ounce of popcorn kernels.</li><li>If you know how much it is for 1 unit of something, it is easy to multiply by the greater quantity to find the price or amount</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
